Joint RT and accuracy patterns in 2AFC tasks can be accounted for by evidence-accumulation models (EAM; see Donkin and Brown, 2018, for a review). EAMs assume that decision-makers sequentially accumulate (noisy) information from their environment that favors one of the available responses. When the amount of information regarding one choice reaches a threshold, accumulation stops, and the decision-maker executes the corresponding response.Fig. 1
