The DDM describes evidence accumulation as a single fractional Gaussian drift process that is bounded by an upper and lower threshold. The process has a starting point denoted by z and drifts with rate v and standard deviation s. The response thresholds are separated by the distance a. Accumulation stops when the process reaches the upper or lower threshold. The time between the beginning and end of the accumulation process is the decision time \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
