As the error rate is determined by the data-generating parameters, we repeatedly generated datasets with different parameter samples until the following criteria were met: 
For Study 1, the empirical error rate was within a margin of 1% around the target error rate (e.g., in the 5%-error scenario, datasets included between 4% and 6% errors). For Studies 2 and 3, the summed difference between empirical and target across conditions was within a margin of 2%.
