For each dataset, the joint posterior distributions of the model parameters were estimated with Bayesian differential-evolution Markov chain Monte Carlo (MCMC) sampling (Turner et al., 2013), as implemented in DMC. Specifically, parameters were estimated using the RUN.dmc function which repeatedly removes and adds samples to the MCMC chains until they converge to their stationary distribution (Heathcote et al., 2019). We ran 3k MCMC chains, where k is the number of free parameters in the model. Each chain was initialized with 120 samples and samples were added and removed in steps of 40 until (a) multivariate \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
